Ramp Studio is a premium cinematic wedding photography website.

Tech Stack:
- Next.js App Router
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion
- next/image

Design Direction:
- luxurious
- cinematic
- editorial
- elegant
- emotional
- immersive
- minimal
- timeless

Visual Identity:
- dark cinematic aesthetic
- warm gold accents
- deep blacks
- soft contrast
- atmospheric imagery
- premium spacing
- refined typography hierarchy

Avoid:
- startup/SaaS UI
- glassmorphism
- colorful cards
- bright gradients
- neon effects
- cluttered layouts
- hard shadows
- flashy animations
- overdesigned UI
- generic templates

Animation Rules:
- smooth
- subtle
- cinematic
- premium
- performance-friendly
- ease-in-out motion
- slow refined transitions

Avoid:
- bouncy motion
- exaggerated transitions
- gimmicky interactions
- aggressive hover scaling
- distracting animations

Typography Rules:
- prioritize typography hierarchy
- elegant spacing between sections
- cinematic editorial feel
- avoid oversized text blocks
- avoid cramped layouts
- maintain strong readability

Layout Rules:
- preserve spacious layouts
- maintain immersive imagery
- use balanced whitespace
- avoid dense grids
- maintain visual rhythm

Code Rules:
- reuse existing components
- avoid unnecessary rewrites
- maintain scalable architecture
- keep components modular
- preserve responsive layouts
- prefer reusable sections/components
- avoid deeply nested JSX
- avoid duplicated logic
- prefer clean Tailwind utility composition

Performance Rules:
- optimize animations
- lazy load heavy assets
- use next/image properly
- avoid unnecessary rerenders
- minimize client components
- preserve smooth scrolling performance

Implementation Rules:
- do not redesign unrelated sections
- modify only necessary files
- explain architectural decisions
- explain modified files
- preserve existing functionality
- avoid unnecessary dependencies

UX Goals:
The website should feel like:
- a luxury cinematic wedding film
- emotionally immersive
- refined and premium
- editorial and timeless
- elegant without feeling corporate

Motion Defaults:
- duration between 0.4s and 0.8s
- use opacity + translate transitions primarily
- avoid excessive scale animation
- prioritize cinematic easing

File Safety Rules:
- never rewrite entire files unnecessarily
- preserve existing responsive behavior
- preserve current imports unless required
- avoid breaking existing sections
- prefer incremental enhancements

Before coding:
- first analyze the existing structure
- explain implementation approach
- identify reusable components
- avoid assumptions

After coding:
- explain modified files
- explain architectural decisions
- explain UX improvements